<h1>@HI{{sore kara}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<p>
<ol>
<li> @Vte{{}} <strong>@HI{{sore kara}}</strong> ...
<li> @Vmasu{{}}  <strong>@HI{{sore kara}}</strong> ...
<li> @Aistem{{}} (@HI{{kute}}) <strong>@HI{{sore kara}}</strong> ...
<li> @Anastem{{}} @HI{{de}} <strong>@HI{{sore kara}}</strong> ...
<li> @N1{{}} (@HI{{to}}) @N2{{}} (@HI{{to}}) <strong>@HI{{sore kara}}</strong> @N3{{}} ...
</ol>
</p>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<strong>@HI{{sore kara}}</strong> is a conjunction that indicates adding to a listing or to a set of states. It means "and then" or "in addition to that".
<p></p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kinou ha @KJ{{two^time^interval}} gurai @KJ{{friend^accomplished}}to @KJ{{drink}}nde <strong>sore kara</strong> uchini @KJ{{homecoming}}rimashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Yesterday I went drinking with my friend for about 2 hours and then went home.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kinou ha @KJ{{two^time^interval}} gurai @KJ{{friend^accomplished}}to @KJ{{drink}}nda. <strong>sore kara</strong> @KJ{{book^roof}}ni @KJ{{draw*near}}tte uchini @KJ{{homecoming}}tta.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Yesterday I drank with my friend for about 2 hours. Then I dropped by a bookstore and then went home.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

<h2> Notes </h2>

@HI{{<strong>sore kara</strong>}} can be used to add an item that the speaker almost forgot to mention.
<p></p>

@HI{{<strong>sore kara</strong>}} can be used by the listener to elicit more information during a story telling: "and then?".
<p></p>

The tense of the clause before @HI{{<strong>sore kara</strong>}} is determined by the tense of the main clause.
<p></p>

